Kenya Needs $2.1 Billion to Build Homes, Roads in Nairobi, Standard Says

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-09-06T04:26:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/kenya-needs-2-1-billion-to-build-homes-roads-in-nairobi-standard-says.html
Kenya ’s capital, Nairobi, needs 200
billion shillings ($2.11 billion) to decongest the city by
building 1.5 million homes, roads and other infrastructure, the
Standard reported, citing Housing Ministry Permanent Secretary
Tirop Kosgei.  A proposed project being considered by the government would
include removing buildings in Nairobi’s Eastlands district and
expanding the central business district, the newspaper said. It
didn’t say when the project would begin or how long it would
take.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  